info.title: Coyote API
info.description:
# Introduction

Welcome to Coyote's API Documentation. You can access our API endpoints, such as Tracking Updates for shipment details,
or Spot Quotes to get rates for high volume shippers who need to quote in bulk. If you have immediate questions or need
more info, please reach out to your Coyote sales rep or
email us at apimanagement@coyote.com.

If you're an existing Coyote customer and want to utilize the API suite, you can request an API key through your Coyote
sales rep.

By accessing or using the Coyote APIs or the API Technical Documentation for the Coyote APIs, you are agreeing to the [Coyote API Terms of Use](https://www.coyote.com/terms-privacy/#api).

## Authentication

Once you've received your API key, you can now access the sandbox environment where you can begin to work with the endpoints.

To retrieve a token, POST to api.coyote.com/connect/token, specifying the following token request parameters:

client_id (provided by integrations team)
client_secret (provided by integrations team)
scope (ExternalApi)
grant_type (client_credentials)

Example:

```
POST /connect/token

    client_id=client1&
    client_secret=api_key&
    grant_type=client_credentials&
    scope=ExternalApi
```

Pass your token as a bearer token in an Authorization header.

Of note:
The API is organized around REST. All requests should be made over SSL. All API request and response bodies are encoded in JSON. Token requests must be form-urlencoded.

To test your requests and responses, use api-sandbox.coyote.com with your sandbox API key.

get.description: Retrieves all of the current details for given load, assuming the provided load are still available.

201.description: Load do not exist or are not available anymore

post.description: Given a set of query inputs, Coyote will return the list of all available loads that match the inputs provided in the request.

201.description: Loads do not exist or are not available anymore

get.summary: Gets an associated document with a load
get.description: Allows Coyote’s partners to retrieve one or more PDF documents in a zipped format for a given Load ID they’re associated to.

200.description: The document successfully retrieved and returned

404.description: The load or the document does not exist

post.summary: Submit a document to be associated with a load
post.description: Allows Coyote’s partners to post one or more documents that will be saved to a given Load ID that they are associated to. Only files up to 20 MB and with specific extensions are allowed. Zips are currently not supported.

200.description: The request was accepted and queued up for saving

404.description: The load or the document does not exist

post.description: Allows Coyote’s partners to submit load requests with relevant load information.

delete.description: Cancel a load that was previously submitted.

get.description: Retrieve the load build status for a previously submitted request.

200.description: The load build status was successfully retrieved

get.summary: Gets all tracking updates for a given load
get.description: Retrieves all tracking updates for a given load, including the dates and last locations tracked or updated by the driver.

200.description: The tracking updates were successfully retrieved

404.description: The tracking updates do not exist

get.summary: Gets the latest tracking update for a given load
get.description: Retrieves the last tracking update for a given load, including the date and last location tracked or updated by the driver.

200.description: The tracking update was successfully retrieved

404.description: The tracking update does not exist

post.description:
Given a set of shipment attributes as input, Coyote will send back a shipment quote with a spot quote ID (“spotQuoteId”). This 
quote includes fuel and will be valid for 5 hours. If you want to proceed with the quote and book a shipment, contact your Coyote rep via phone
or email and refer to the Quote ID.

200.description: The spot quote was successfully retrieved

x-code-samples.source:
curl -k -H 'Content-Type: application/json'\
-H 'Authorization: Bearer TOKEN'\
-X POST -d '{
  "EquipmentTypeId": "V",
  "Origin": {
    "CityName": "Chicago",
    "StateCode": "IL",
    "CountryCode": "US",
    "PostalCode": "60647"
  },
  "Destination": {
    "CityName": "Madison",
    "StateCode": "WI",
    "CountryCode": "US",
    "PostalCode": "53703"
  },
  "PickUpDateUTC": "2020-06-08T19:07:01.5291744Z",
  "MinTemperature": null,
  "MaxTemperature": null,
  "Weight": 100.0,
  "Commodity": "Sample Commodity",
  "EquipmentLength": 53.0,
  "IsHazmat": false,
  "IsDropTrailer": false,
  "CustomerShipmentId": "CUST1234"
}' 'https://api-sandbox.coyote.com/api/v1/SpotQuotes'

HttpResponse response = Unirest.post("https://api-sandbox.coyote.com/api/v1/SpotQuotes")
.header("content-type", "application/json")
.header("Authorization", "Bearer TOKEN")
.body("{
  "EquipmentTypeId": "V",
  "Origin": {
    "CityName": "Chicago",
    "StateCode": "IL",
    "CountryCode": "US",
    "PostalCode": "60647"
  },
  "Destination": {
    "CityName": "Madison",
    "StateCode": "WI",
    "CountryCode": "US",
    "PostalCode": "53703"
  },
  "PickUpDateUTC": "2020-06-08T19:07:01.5291744Z",
  "MinTemperature": null,
  "MaxTemperature": null,
  "Weight": 100.0,
  "Commodity": "Sample Commodity",
  "EquipmentLength": 53.0,
  "IsHazmat": false,

  "CustomerShipmentId": "CUST1234"
}")
.asString();

post.description:
Given a set of shipment attributes as input, Coyote will send back an LTL shipment quote with an LTL spot quote ID (“ltlSpotQuoteId”). This 
quote includes the list of carriers and their respective quotes and is valid for 7 days. If you want to proceed with the specific quote and book a shipment, contact your Coyote rep via phone
or email and refer to the LTL Spot Quote ID along with the Carrier Quote ID.
